entries.title: The Old Power Station
entries.propertyDescription: Overlooking the River Thames, we have two units becoming available from December ranging from just under 700-square-foot to 860-square-foot of office space. The site is conveniently located within a 5-minute walk from Barnes Bridge railway station and a 10-minute walk from Mortlake station, both offering trains to Clapham Junction and Waterloo. The area is surrounded by a variety of shops, cafÃ©s, and pubs. Tideway Yard also features the renowned Rick Stein Restaurant, known for its stunning river views. The complex offers direct access to the Thames Path and the site includes a shared meeting room available to book.

entries.title: Unit 6, Stephendale Yard
entries.propertyDescription:
Newly refurbished self-contained commercial space ready for occupancy imminently, providing 915 ft of contemporary workspace suitable for small businesses. The open-plan unit, has been fitted out to a high standard, with a new kitchenette and two WCs.

Situated in a commercial complex off Stephendale Road, within a courtyard development. Additionally, there are available car parking spaces and bike storage. For further details, please feel free to reach out.

entries.title: T22 Tideway Yard
entries.propertyDescription:
Recently renovated, this unit occupies the space above the archway in the courtyard complex, the commercial space blends seamlessly its characterful features with modern requirements. The split-level layout boasts an open-plan design with a dedicated meeting room, kitchenette, WC's, and scenic river views. Additionally, the unit includes designated parking and access to a communal meeting room with views of the River Thames.

Nestled amidst the serene riverside setting, the business complex provides direct access to the River Thames, creating a tranquil workspace complemented by nearby amenities. These amenities encompass an on-site Rick Steins restaurant, local coffee spots like Orange Pekoe, charming neighborhood pubs, and convenient nearby facilities.

entries.title: T01A Tideway Yard
entries.propertyDescription:
This commercial unit is situated within a courtyard complex with direct access to Mortlake High Street. The two-story building can be leased as a single unit or divided into two smaller units, each approximately 500 sq ft, connected by a spiral staircase. Both units include kitchenette and WC facilities, as well as access to a meeting room overlooking the River Thames.

Nestled in the serene surroundings of the riverside, this business complex offers direct access to the River Thames, providing a tranquil workspace enhanced by nearby amenities. These amenities include an on-site Rick Steins restaurant, local coffee establishments such as Orange Pekoe, charming neighborhood pubs, and convenient nearby shops.

entries.title: Foundry Mews
entries.propertyDescription:
Nestled discreetly along the charming stretch of Barnes High Street lies Foundry Mews a courtyard development. The commercial complex offers a harmonious blend of contemporary workspace set amidst serene surroundings. Developed and managed by Marston Properties, this modern workspace seamlessly provides a tranquil environment ideal for small businesses to thrive.

We have availability of two commercial units in Autumn 2024, ranging from 775 to 850 sq ft. For further information please contact Marston Properties.

entries.title: Tideway Yard
entries.propertyDescription:
Established in 1901, Tideway Yard has undergone a remarkable transformation from its origins as a stables and coach house to become a distinctive commercial destination. This self-contained building spans 4,500 sq ft across three floors, seamlessly blending contemporary office spaces with its rich historical character. Nestled along Mortlake High Street, it offers direct access to the picturesque River Thames, creating a serene workspace environment. Complete with kitchenettes, restrooms, parking facilities, and scheduled availability in Q3 2024.

Please see the attached brochure for further details

entries.title: 518 Wandsworth Road, Cafe
entries.propertyDescription:
518 Wandsworth Road is situated on the northside of Wandsworth Road next to the The Plough Brewery on the junction with Silverthorne Road, immediately opposite the junction with North Street.
The area benefits from excellent transport links with Queenstown Road overground station providing a direct service to both Vauxhall and Clapham Junction. Wandsworth Road overground station is just a 2-minute walk away providing access to Greater London. The area is also well catered for with local bus services providing links to the surrounding areas.

Ground floor newly developed cafÃ© space which forms part of a Grade II listed building which will be left in a shell and core condition. The cafÃ© benefits from an outdoor seating area to the front plus indoor seating for up to 50 people.
